      • IsUserAllowToPerformThisOperation

        public int IsUserAllowToPerformThisOperation(java.lang.String userName)

        Method Description

        This method checks and returns Integer value if the present logged-in user has the access level or right to perform a specific operation in the application.
        Parameters:
        ibUser - It accepts the IBApplicationUser class object as its parameter
        Returns:
        It returns an integer value with the following interpretations;
        • 0 if user group is System Default (which can perform CRUD operations on both Identities AND Users)
        • 1 if user group is Administrator (which can perform CRUD operations on both Identities AND Users)
        • 2 if user group is Power (which can perform only CRUD operation on Identities and NOT Users
        • 3 if user group is Viewer (which can perform Read only operations on Identities NOT Users

      • getLoggedInUserInformation

        public static void getLoggedInUserInformation(java.lang.String userName)

        Method Description

        This method retrieves the User details from the Database and sets them to the application MDI which are shown in the Status bar. This will help to know the logged-in user profile name and user group as well.
        Parameters:
        userName - It takes a String of the Username as its parameter.

      • getCRUDOperationToPerform

        public boolean getCRUDOperationToPerform(javax.swing.JRadioButton createRadioButton,
                                         javax.swing.JRadioButton readRadioButton,
                                         javax.swing.JRadioButton updateRadioButton,
                                         javax.swing.JRadioButton deleteRadioButton)

        Method Description

        The method will check to for which CRUD operation the User has selected to use in the application. It accepts four (4) items as its parameters of the object type JRadioButton
        Parameters:
        createRadioButton - The radio button for the Create operation
        readRadioButton - The radio button for the Read operation
        updateRadioButton - The radio button for the Update operation
        deleteRadioButton - The radio button for the Delete operation
        Returns:
        Returns true if there is a selected radio button else return false
